<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Mik Management - Welcome</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="hero">
      <div class="hero__content">
        <h1>Welcome to Mik Management</h1>
        <p>Your quick start guide to running the registration portal locally.</p>
        <a class="button" href="/register">Go to Registration</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container">
      <section>
        <h2>Installation Guide</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Install <strong>Node.js</strong> version 18 or newer from the official website.</li>
          <li>Clone this repository with <code>git clone &lt;repository-url&gt;</code>.</li>
          <li>Open the project folder and run <code>npm install</code> to install dependencies.</li>
          <li>Start the server with <code>npm start</code>.</li>
          <li>Visit <a href="http://localhost:3000">http://localhost:3000</a> in your browser.</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Essential Git Usage</h2>
        <p>The following commands are all you need to collaborate with this project:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><code>git status</code> – check what changed.</li>
          <li><code>git add .</code> – stage your updates.</li>
          <li><code>git commit -m "Describe your change"</code> – save your work.</li>
          <li><code>git push origin main</code> – publish your commit to the remote repository.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Always pull the latest updates with <code>git pull</code> before you start a new change.</p>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="footer">
      <p>&copy; <span id="year"></span> Mik Management. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>

    <script>
      document.getElementById('year').textContent = new Date().getFullYear();
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
